title: For Sale:  EM-GE Model 5 over/under derringer
postcontent:
This is an EM-GE Model 5 over and under derringer. I could not determine the origin from the proof marks, but I believe this gun was made in England or Belgium. There are no markings other than EM-GE Mod. 5 on the right hand side of the frame and the caliber designation on the left. There is no serial number. It closely resembles a Colt .25 automatic in size and shape and appears to be a well made, high quality piece (the photos are much larger than the actual pistol). It is in caliber .320, a British cartridge, which is the equivalent of an American .32 short Colt cartridge. I cannot guarantee that the Colt cartridge will fit as in some .320s it does and in others it does not. The overall condition is very good, with just a very few pit marks and most of the bluing intact.

If you like to collect small pistols this would make an interesting and unusual addition to your collection. Face to Face transactions only.

title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson 520 - RARE - NYSP - New York State Police
postcontent:
This gun is a must have for any serious Smith & Wesson collector

In 1979 the New York State Police ordered 3000 custom "N" Model 520's with fixed sights but they cancelled the order before delivery was made. 

S&W was well into production so they completed the run and in 1980 they were made available to the general public. To this day the Model 520 is the only N Frame, S&W 357 Magnum Revolver ever built with fixed sights 

This one is in new condition and I believe that it has never been fired. The original box has seen better days but it is correctly numbered to the gun.

Metal work is in good condition (much better than average, thought the bolt sticks a little on extraction, may just need a deep cleaning, I've not investigated).  Stock needs either serious work or replacement.   There's a crack under the action (not serious), and the front is warped about 10-20 degrees out of alignment. Hang Tag - USMC Sgt A. Arguello (I presume this is who brought it home).    I'll email photos on request.

title: For Sale:  H&K P7 PSP "Squeeze Cocker" - Matching Orig. Box/ Manual/ Tools + Leather Paddle Holster
postcontent:
Hello!  Listed here is a somewhat rare and amazing firearm.  This is the H&K P7 PSP (Police Model) in 9mm (9x19mm).

There is a great history behind these pistols.  After the Munich Olympics, Germany went through a total revision of its firearms, 1 of which was the procurement of a new standardized pistol for the military and police.  This pistol was developed as a result of those trials.

If you have watched Die Hard you remember "Hanz" wielding one of these ! :)

This particular pistol has been in my collection for some time.  It comes with the original matching serial numbered box, gas chamber brush and disassemble tool as well as the original manual.

NOTE that when you look for these, you will find many of them were refinished at the H&K Arsenal and now have what is called the "plum" colored slide.  This handgun DOES NOT have that appearance and is in the original 90-95% condition finish.

This also comes with a VERY nice leather OWB paddle holster made by Wild Bill Holsters.

I am not interested in trading unless you have an AR-15 in 7.62x39 caliber or I will put cash towards a Robinson Arms XCR-L in either .223 or 7.62x39

Contact info is below.  Thanks for looking and let me know if you have any questions.

postcontent: I have a Stevens Model 311A 12 gauge side by side double barrel.  The wood is in great shape and metal in good condition.  This gun has the double triggers.  I am almost certain it has one modified choke barrel and one full choke barrel.  This DB does not have a serial number so it is definately older than 1968.  Not sure of exact age but doing some reading, their is 17A in a circle on the bottom near the forearm.  If this is the date code - it would be 1949 model.  It has an I in a circle under the barrels so if this is the date code it is a 1957 model.  Either way it is 1949 - 1957 model somewhere.  Gun shoots great.

postcontent:
***First and foremost, I understand that this type of ad is out of the ordinary, and what I'm looking for might open the flood gates to many different suggestions and opinions as to what I should do. Please understand that I've done a lot of soul searching and even more research. Every person has their feelings on the matter, but what it boils down to is that this is an ad NOT a forum. While I respect every firearm owner’s opinion and their right to have one, to that same regard, I would hope that you would respect mine. Please do not respond with advice rather than a genuine offer or question about the firearms listed.***



  This is a large majority of my firearms collection. I have decided to consolidate after realizing that I am only one man and can only shoot one gun at a time. To the same respect, I'm looking to shoot more often on fewer platforms. Restricting myself to only higher quality, higher end pieces. If I diminish my collection from many to few, I want those few to be the very best out there at what they do. I like to think of myself as a VERY diverse shooter. I enjoy the sport of shooting and am open to many different venues, situations, and purposes: Home Defense, Competition, Target, Etc. With that being said...My goal is to trade up, not to sell. I have no problem offering multiple firearms in exchange for one, as long as the VALUE and QUALITY is there. Every firearm I own is in excellent condition or brand new. Nothing on this list is below 95%+ condition and most are way above (unless noted). The prices listed next to each piece are fair middle ground prices. I could start high with the expectation to be bartered with, but why not skip all the BS and cut to the chase. Please do not contact me expecting to be able to pay the lowest price listed, as again, I'm not really looking to sell. I understand that due to location and demographic, the values I have listed may be lower or higher then what is available in your area. I would like to think I am a reasonable person. If you believe I'm too low or too high please let me know and depending on what you're offering we may be able to work something out. I'm not in any hurry to get rid of any piece so please no low ball offers. I'm looking for straight value for value here. If you believe your offer to have higher than expected value, please explain why. That is why I'm here, to get the best of the best.

 What I'm looking for:

 1911's (for carry, competition, HD, etc)... Brands I'm interested in: Wilson Combat, Nighthawk Custom, Les Baer, Ed Brown, Colt, Dan Wesson. 

 AR-15 Platform (anything from LD, to target, to tactical)... Brands I'm interested in: Noveske, POF, Les Baer, Colt, Sabre, BCM, LMT

 I am an experienced shooter, but I'm far from an expert. I ALWAYS love learning about new firearms and platforms. If you have a firearm that isn't listed above, but think it meets the expectations of what I'm looking for, then please tell me about it and I would be happy to do some research.
